{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9770dd6d-ede2-4223-a724-28aae372bcf8","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"85cc70ea-ba7d-49b6-8844-8fbb8b37f2cb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":317,"requestId":"A02E:3B0D3D:191E833:1C670E0:69FE8A1E"},"id":"1193af06-ca72-4a4b-8475-001ba9ecf8da","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:13:09.006Z","parentId":"f608b6e2-9ad7-4cb0-ba33-3e2b6afd2be6"}
